\u00e2teau, is located on the southern tip of the [[Cap d'Antibes]] in 22 acres of pine trees and tropical gardens.<ref name=\"dailymail.co.uk\">Andrea Catherwood (December 4, 2011), [http://www.dailymail.co.uk/travel/article-2069851/Cote-DAzur-breaks-Timeless-glamour-Hotel-du-Cap-Eden-Roc.html#ixzz1k7fj1rY0 Eternal chic: A holiday with the jet-set at the Cote D'Azur's iconic Hotel du Cap-Eden-Roc] ''[[Daily Mail]]''.</ref> It houses 117 suites starting at USD $1,300 per night.<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\"/> In addition, there are two private villas, the Villa Eleana (in front of the property) priced at USD $10,000 per night and the Villa Les C\u00e8dres priced at $15,000 per night. Owner Maja Oetker decorates the rooms and suites.<ref name=\"Splendor on the Riviera\"/> In 2011, the hotel underwent a $67 million renovation. Within the complex there are six clay tennis courts, a spa, fitness center, shopping, hair dresser and nine acres of lush greenery. The swimming pool is a heated salt water pool, cut into the edge of the cliff in 1914.<ref name=\"dailymail.co.uk\"/> Thirty-three [[Cabana (structure)|cabana]]s are located in the rock facing the sea.\n\n==Management==\nThe H\u00f4tel du Cap-Eden-Roc belongs to the [[Oetker Collection]]. The Oetker Collection is managed by the [[Dr. Oetker|Oetker]] family.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20040830031403/http://www.edenroc-hotel.fr/ Hotel du Cap-Eden-Roc official site]\n{{Commons category|H\u00f4tel du Cap-Eden-Roc}}\n\n{{coord|43|32|53|N|7|07|14|E|source:kolossus-frwiki|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Hotels in France|Cap]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Antibes]]\n[[Category:Dr. Oetker]]\n[[Category:Hotels established in 1870|Cap]]\n[[Category:1870 establishments in France]]\n", "name_user": "William Avery", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel_du_Cap"}
